canonical:
  title: 初到官上按察使狀
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 謫來卑濕茫若墮空仰止高明確如倚岳恭惟按部使臣長才經遠淳德鎭浮夙荷聖知依日光於漢殿出爲天使流星彩於蜀都恩如春之溫溫威不寒而凜凜某謬分憂寄幸託仁庥苟可謁於征軒豈辭重繭顧有拘於官守未得奮飛
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 初到官上按察使狀
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 謫來卑濕。茫若墮空。仰止高明。確如倚岳。恭惟按部使臣。長才經遠。淳德鎭浮。夙荷聖知。依日光於漢殿。出爲天使。流星彩於蜀都。恩如春之溫溫。威不寒而凜凜。某謬分憂寄。幸託仁庥。苟可謁於征軒。豈辭重繭。顧有拘於官守。未得奮飛。
korean:
  title: 초도관 상 안찰사 장
  author: 이규보
  language: kor
  text: 낮고 습한 땅에 귀양을 오니 아득하여 공중에서 떨어진 것과 같고, 고명하신 어른을 우러름에 든든하여 산악에 기댄 듯합니다. 삼가 생각건대, 안부사신(按部使臣)은 재주가 높아 먼일을 경륜하고, 덕이 순박하여 들뜨고 경박한 습속을 바로잡았으며, 일찍이 임금의 알아줌을 받아 한전(漢殿)에서 일광(日光)을 의지하였고, 사신이 되어 외국에 나가 촉도(蜀都)에서 성채(星彩)를 빛냈음에 은정은 봄과 같이 따뜻하고, 위엄은 차갑지 않아도 늠름합니다. 모(某)는 그릇되이 지방관의 책임을 맡아, 다행히 어지신 덕에 의탁하였는데 진실로 가서 뵐 수 있다면 어찌 발이 부르틈을 꺼리겠습니까만, 직책에 얽매인 몸이므로 뜻을 이루지 못합니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0510_010_0410&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: A Respectful Petition Upon First Taking Official Post to the Inspector of the Path
  author: Lee Gyu-bo
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Banished to these lowlands, damp and mean, I drifted as one falling through the void. Yet gazing upon your excellence, my heart steadies like a man leaning against mountains.

    I humbly reflect: You, noble Inspector, possess talents vast enough to govern distant lands. Your virtues are pure, rectifying the frivolous ways of lesser spirits. Long favored by the throne, you stood bathed in imperial light within the Han palace. Sent forth as envoy, you bore the brilliance of stars over the lands of Shu. Your grace flows warm as spring itself, while your authority—though not harsh—commands solemn reverence.

    I, unworthy as I am, have been entrusted with the burden of provincial charge, and fortunately shelter beneath your benevolent shadow. Should fortune allow me to pay you proper respects, how could I hesitate, though my feet bear the weight of a thousand miles? Yet bound as I am by the duties of my post, I cannot give wings to my desires.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'lowlands, damp and mean' likely refers to the author's place of exile or provincial posting.
  - key: ''
    value: The Han palace and Shu refer to the imperial court and distant territories respectively, suggesting the inspector's high rank and wide experience.
  - key: ''
    value: '''Bearing the weight of a thousand miles'' is an idiom expressing willingness to undergo hardship.'
